<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5–2748: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-28T19:00:00-04:00">May 28, 1948—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>809. It is assumed that after consultation with FonOff (Embtel 962 May 27
                            and Deptel 799 May 28) and before taking action indicated you will
                            appropriately inform your British and French colleagues.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>